nate (variable)">indeterminates</a> (also called <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Variable_(mathematics)" title=3D"Variable (mathematics)">var=
iables</a>) and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coefficient" title=
=3D"Coefficient">coefficients</a>, that involves only the operations of <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addition" title=3D"Addition">addition=
</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subtraction" title=3D"Subtra=
ction">subtraction</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplica=
tion" title=3D"Multiplication">multiplication</a> and <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation" title=3D"Exponentiation">exponentiation=
</a> to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonnegative_integer" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Nonnegative integer">nonnegative integer</a> powe=
rs, and has a finite number of terms.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polynomial#cite_note-1"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
