</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A <i>polynomial expression</i> is an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Expression_(mathematics)" title=3D"Expression (mathematics)">expressi=
on</a> that can be built from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cons=
tant_(mathematics)" title=3D"Constant (mathematics)">constants</a> and symb=
ols called <i>variables</i> or <i>indeterminates</i> by means of <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addition" title=3D"Addition">addition</a>, <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplication" title=3D"Multiplica=
tion">multiplication</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expon=
entiation" title=3D"Exponentiation">exponentiation</a> to a <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-negative_integer" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Non-negative integer">non-negative integer</a> power. The constants are=
 generally <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number" title=3D"Number=
">numbers</a>, but may be any expression that do not involve the indetermin=
ates, and represent <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_o=
bject" title=3D"Mathematical object">mathematical objects</a> that can be a=
dded and multiplied. Two polynomial expressions are considered as defining =
the same <i>polynomial</i> if they may be transformed, one to the other, by=
 applying the usual properties of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Commutative_property" title=3D"Commutative property">commutativity</a>, <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Associative_property" title=3D"Associ=
ative property">associativity</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Distributive_property" title=3D"Distributive property">distributivity</=
a> of addition and multiplication. For example <span class=3D"mwe-math-elem=
ent mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math=
-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/199=
8/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle (x-1)(x-2)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
