ion" title=3D"Rational function">rational functions</a></i>, depending on c=
ontext.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Polynomial#cite_note-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>  This is analogous to=
 the fact that the ratio of two <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In=
teger" title=3D"Integer">integers</a> is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Rational_number" title=3D"Rational number">rational number</a>, no=
t necessarily an integer.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-24" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
