<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Exponential_polynomials">Ex=
ponential polynomials</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.ph=
p?title=3DPolynomial&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D19" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Exponential polynomials"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A bivariate polynomial where the second variable is substituted for an e=
xponential function applied to the first variable, for example <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>P</i>(<i>x</i>, <i>e</i><sup><i>x</i></sup>)</span>, may be=
 called an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponential_polynomial"=
 title=3D"Exponential polynomial">exponential polynomial</a>.
</p>
